The Vlaamse Sportfederatie vzw (VSF) is the recognized umbrella organisation of the sports federations in Flanders (Belgium). VSF supports, informs and represents more than 75 sports federations, their approx. 19.000 clubs and over 1,4 million club members.&#xd;
&#xd;
VSF has 7 thematic focuses: sports policy, support to the governance of the member federations, sports for all, elite sport, volunteering in sport, sports and ethics, sports and health, support to sports clubs management.&#xd;
&#xd;
You will find on www.Vlaamsesportfederatie.be an overview of its member organisations and staff members.&#xd;
